ENUGU – The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has expressed commitment to partner with the Enugu State Ministry of Transport to further reduce road crashes in the state. The Sector Commander of FRSC Enugu State Command, Mr. Joseph Toby, disclosed this during a courtesy call he paid to the Permanent Secretary of the ministry, Mr. Ogbonna Idike, on Tuesday in Enugu. Toby noted that the two organizations needed to work harmoniously to make life easier for motorists and other road users in the state. FRSC Clarifies Alleged Promotion Racketeering Heavy Traffic: FRSC Tasked To Dismantle Roadblocks On… “We have come a long way in our relationship and collaboration over the years. “However, my visit here is to further synergise and deepen the partnership in terms of easing traffic within the state. “We also going to work with this ministry and its traffic control arm on the evacuation of broken-down vehicles and ensuring motorists abide by road rules and regulation,” he said. Responding, Idike said that the ministry was particularly concerned about synergy in the area of training and re-training of its Enugu State Traffic Management Agency (ESTMA) officers. “The ministry believes that such training and re-training of ESTMA officers would ensure professionalism as well as improve quality service delivery to the good people of the state. POLL “We are also looking at robust collaboration in other traffic programmes within the state,” he said. The permanent secretary thanked Toby and his principal officers for coming to the ministry notwithstanding their tight official schedules. The high point of the visit was a group photograph between principal officers of FRSC and top ministry officials.